com.ericramirezs.commando4j.arguments

Interface IArgument<A extends IArgument,T>

  • Type Parameters:
    A - Self argument object that implements IArgument.
    T - result object after parsing the argument.
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AnnouncementChannelArgument, Argument, AudioChannelArgument, BooleanArgument, CategoryChannelArgument, ChannelArgument, CommandArgument, CustomEmojiArgument, FloatArgument, GuildArgument, IntegerArgument, LocalDateArgument, LocalTimeArgument, MemberArgument, MessageArgument, MessageChannelArgument, RoleArgument, StageChannelArgument, StringArgument, TextChannelArgument, ThreadChannelArgument, UnionArgument, URLArgument, UserArgument, VoiceChannelArgument

    public interface IArgument<A extends IArgument,T>
    Interface to implement in any object to be used as an argument for a Command.

    An argument refers to any text entered by the user after the command name, which will be used to make a command function perform certain functions based on these arguments.

    The goal of the implementation is to manage the validation and conversion of the parameter to a specific object, to simplify the development of the command.

    See Also:
    ICommand
